# Up Final UI Rule

## Visual Direction
- Maintain ultra-minimal dark foundation and high-contrast readability.
- Keep visual language consistent across cards, charts, and data surfaces.
- Prefer token-driven consistency over one-off styling.

## Component Discipline
- Components stay presentational and composable.
- Move domain logic and side effects to hooks/stores/services.
- Avoid monolithic components; split by responsibility.

## Styling Constraints
- Tailwind CSS is the only styling system for components.
- No inline styles unless there is a strict runtime requirement.
- Keep tokens and utility patterns aligned with `tailwind.config.ts`.

## i18n Hard Rule
- Do not hardcode user-facing copy in components.
- Route all UI copy through i18n key lookup.
- New features must define and use translation keys from day one.
